    "The examined input variable affects the output variable positively when the respective relevancy factor has a positive value.",
    "The reverse occurs when this factor has a negative sign.",
    "Accordingly, the influence of a parameter on the output variable increases with the increment of the respective relevancy factor regardless of its sign.",
    "The effects of the input variables on the amounts of hydrogen storage capacity by calculating the relevancy factor of each parameter are shown in Fig. 6.",
    "Based on the obtained results, the amounts of Sn, Co, and Ni elements in the AB 2 metal hydrides have the greatest impact on the hydrogen storage capacity."
